CBS News White House Correspondent Weijia Jiang took issue with President Trump when he called on the public to protect the Asian American community and not blame it for the coronavirus.
Suggesting that message was derogatory toward Asians, she tweeted, “Trump: Asian *Americans* need protection.
pic.twitter.com/BrN6yfTkCu — Weijia Jiang (@weijia) March 23, 2020Her tweet came on the heels of a Trump tweet calling for the Asian American community to be protected.
“This morning a White House official referred to #Coronavirus as the “Kung-Flu” to my face,” she tweeted on March 17.
“Makes me wonder what they’re calling it behind my back.”This morning a White House official referred to #Coronavirus as the “Kung-Flu” to my face.